sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: JAMT
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: SAM:jasmonic acid carboxyl methyltransferase; converts jasmonic acid to jasmine odor
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephen Payne
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This ORF encodes the enzyme responsible for catalyzing the following reaction: Jasmonic Acid--->Methyl Jasmonate It is initially found in ''Arabidopsis thaliana'' but has been transferred successfully to the E. coli genome by Seo, et al. The product, methyl jasmonate has a jasmine smell to it.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Km: 38.5 ??M; Kcat:25 S−1 for Jasmonic Acid--->Methyl Jasmonate with the aid of JAMT: Jasmonic acid carboxyl methyltransferase
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: If the part becomes physically available, it would probably be donated by Seo, et al.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Wintergree
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Exponential phase dependent wintergreen odor generator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephen Payne
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part converts salicylic acid into methyl salicylate (a mint-smelling compound) in the exponential phase of cell growth. The part consists of a stationary phase promoter (J45992), connected to an inverter (Q04401) as well as the methyl salicylate protein generator (J45119). This part replaces the defective part J45180, which used the truncated version of the stationary phase promoter (J45993). This part did not function as it was designed due to an imbalance between the strength of the stationary phase promoter and the strength of the promoter in the inverter (R0040).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We needed the full osmY promoter strength to be relatively comparable to the R0040 promoter strength.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Yes. It comes from many subparts.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephen Payne
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This composite part consists of <bbrick>J45992</bbrick> (a stationary phase promoter), <bbrick>Q04401</bbrick> (an inverter), and E0840 (a green fluorescent protein generator). This device expresses GFP in the exponential phase of cell growth.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This device was constructed to test whether the J45180 device would work.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: J45992 was PCRed out of the E. coli genome, while Q04401 and E0840 were developed by others in the Registry.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: EWOBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Exponential phase wintergreen odor biosynthetic system
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: MIT iGEM 2006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This system designed by the MIT 2006 iGEM team generates mint smell by biosynthesizing salicylic acid from chassis-produced metabolites (chorismate) and then converts salicylic acid into methyl salicylate (wintergreen scent). It uses a stationary phase promoter followed by an inverter (see <bbpart>BBa_J45996<bbpart> for details) to only express the necessary enzymes during exponential phase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We recommend use of strain <bbpart>BBa_J45999</bbpart> as it does not produce indole. Indole is responsible for the foul smell of wt e.coli, and masks the wintergreen scent produced by J45800.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is composed of <bbpart>BBa_J45320</bbpart> and <bbpart>BBa_J45180</bbpart>
